<div id="ctr"> <div id="hd"> <h1> Neuroscience For Kids </h1> </div>

<div id="mn"> <h2> brain awareness week </h2>

<img src="baw/bawnewi.gif" alt="" class="flr" /><p>
 Brain Awareness Week (BAW) is a nationwide effort organized by the <a 
href="http://www.dana.org/brainweek" title="EXTERNAL LINK - dana.org 
website">Dana Foundation</a> and the <a 
href="http://www.sfn.org/BAW/" title="EXTERNAL LINK - Society for 
Neuroscience website">Society for Neuroscience</a> to promote the public 
and personal benefits of brain research.  The official week for the next 
BAW is <strong>March 11-17, 2024</strong>, but any week is a good time 
to get involved. </p>

<h3>The Brain Rocks: A New BAW Activity</h3>

<p>To participate, all you have to do is find a rock and paint it with a 
drawing of a brain or a neuron.  It would be great if you could add a few 
words such as "BAW 2024" or "Brain Awareness Week."  Then put your brain 
rock outside and take a photo of it.  Please do not include any people 
in your photos; just your brain rock.</p><p>

<a 
href="https://padlet.com/chudler/the-brain-rocks-nyoasc2tfaiopl5z">Upload 
your photo</a> by clicking on the small + in the circle at the bottom of 
the <a 
href="https://padlet.com/chudler/the-brain-rocks-nyoasc2tfaiopl5z"> 
Brain Rocks Padlet</a>.  Here is an example brain rock:</p> <p><img 
src="gif/brainrock.jpg" width="442" height="330"></p>

<p>For 2024 Brain Awareness Week, we will host a "Speakers Bureau" with 
University of Washington neuroscientists interested in discussing their 
work with students. Teachers can now <a 
href="bawspeakers24.html">request a neuroscientist</a> to speak with 
their students.  </p>

